result.name: HIGE Izakaya

reviews.text: Delicious food! Everything was good. We especially loved the clam soup, sake was good, and the crab-and-egg was unique. My favorites were the liver and tongue skewers—best liver and tongue I’ve ever had in my life!

A little pricey but this cosy place has some really tasty small bites. Particular favourites from our trip were the chicken cartilage, the ox tongue and the chicken meatball. The restaurant doesn’t seat many people and only has four tables and a bar counter so a booking is needed especially if you want to go during peak times.
Great neighborhood restaurant. Fresh food and decent prices.
Not bad but expensive
I don’t dislike here but not too impressive. It’s an average quality Izakaya though premium pricing.
